40|$|This {{bachelor}} {{thesis is}} focusing on an employee <b>benefits</b> <b>system</b> and its functionality. Theoretical part of the thesis specifies the human resources field as a whole, and its particular aspects, considering mainly the employee remuneration and employee <b>benefits</b> <b>system.</b> It also expands {{on the relationship between}} motivation, employee benefits and employee remuneration. The established knowledge are used in a practical part of the thesis, which has been carried out in H 1 s. r. o. The company is first introduced, with both the current situation, as well as its historical development described, and the thesis then outlines the current employee benefits based on a undertaken survey and also analyses the collected data. At the end of the practical part, the recommendations and suggestions for improvements of the particular aspects of employee <b>benefits</b> <b>system</b> functioning are listed...|$|R
